<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 1:21PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...Showers will impact portions of southern Tuscola, Lapeer, Wayne,
Oakland, western Macomb, eastern Genesee and eastern Washtenaw
Counties through 245 PM EDT...
At 118 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking showers along a line
extending from near Millington to near Clarkston to Belleville.
Movement was northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail and wind gusts to 25 MPH.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
Showers with small hail will be near...
Millington, Otter Lake and Clarkston around 130 PM EDT.
Ortonville around 140 PM EDT.
Oxford and Mayville around 155 PM EDT.
Romulus and Canton around 200 PM EDT.
Taylor and Metamora around 210 PM EDT.
Greenfield Village around 215 PM EDT.
Livonia around 225 PM EDT.
Dearborn and Dryden around 230 PM EDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Expect some brief intervals of small hail.</instruction>
